author: I Gede Morgan Semone
label: Tree 1
location: Jl. Kertanegara, Ubung Kaja, Kec. Denpasar Utara, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80115, Indonesia
subject: Ficus benjamina (Beringin / Banyan)
description: Ficus benjamina, commonly known as the Beringin or Banyan, is a popular indoor and outdoor ornamental tree. Renowned for its graceful, drooping branches and lush, glossy leaves, it thrives in warm climates. It’s often used in landscaping and interior design, symbolizing prosperity and providing excellent air purification.

subject: Alstonia scholaris (Pulai / Pule)
description: Alstonia scholaris, known as Pulai or Pule, is a tall, evergreen tree native to Southeast Asia. It features glossy, dark green leaves and clusters of fragrant white flowers. Often used in traditional medicine, it also provides valuable timber. The tree is respected for its medicinal properties and its role in local ecosystems.

subject: Ceiba pentandra (Kapok tree)
description: Ceiba pentandra, commonly called the Kapok tree, is a majestic, towering tropical tree with a broad, spreading canopy. It produces large, fluffy seed fibers known as kapok, used as stuffing and insulation. The tree’s striking appearance and ecological importance make it a vital part of rainforest environments, symbolizing strength and resilience.
